Here's how to handle each scenario with MSTest:

## 1. Windows-Only Tests — Custom `TestMethod` Attribute

```csharp
[AttributeUsage(AttributeTargets.Method)]
public class WindowsOnlyTestMethodAttribute : TestMethodAttribute
{
    public override TestResult[] Execute(ITestMethod testMethod)
    {
        if (!RuntimeInformation.IsOSPlatform(OSPlatform.Windows))
        {
            return new[]
            {
                new TestResult { Outcome = UnitTestOutcome.Inconclusive,
                                 TestFailureException = new AssertInconclusiveException(
                                     "Test requires Windows.") }
            };
        }
        return base.Execute(testMethod);
    }
}

[WindowsOnlyTestMethod]
public void Registry_ReadsExpectedValue() { /* ... */ }
```

## 2. Skip in CI — Category + Environment Check

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void Render_ProducesExpectedOutput()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") is not null)
    {
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU.");
    }
    // ...
}
```

Then in CI, you can also exclude by filter:
```bash
dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"
```

## 3. Flaky External API — `[Retry]` (MSTest 3.8+)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)] // retries up to 3 times on failure
public async Task GetWeather_ReturnsValidForecast()
{
    var result = await _weatherClient.GetForecastAsync("Seattle");
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}
```

For older MSTest versions, implement retry in a custom `TestMethodAttribute`:

```csharp
public class RetryTestMethodAttribute : TestMethodAttribute
{
    public int MaxRetries { get; }
    public RetryTestMethodAttribute(int maxRetries = 3) => MaxRetries = maxRetries;

    public override TestResult[] Execute(ITestMethod testMethod)
    {
        TestResult[]? results = null;
        for (int i = 0; i < MaxRetries; i++)
        {
            results = base.Execute(testMethod);
            if (results.All(r => r.Outcome == UnitTestOutcome.Passed))
                return results;
        }
        return results!;
    }
}
```

## 4. Cleanup Temp Files — `[TestCleanup]`

`[TestCleanup]` runs **even when the test fails**:

```csharp
[TestClass]
public class FileProcessorTests
{
    private string _tempFile = null!;

    [TestInitialize]
    public void Setup()
    {
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    [TestCleanup]
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void Process_WritesExpectedOutput()
    {
        File.WriteAllText(_tempFile, "input");
        var result = FileProcessor.Process(_tempFile);
        Assert.AreEqual("expected", result);
    }
}
```

---

**Summary of patterns:**

| Scenario | Approach |
|----------|----------|
| OS-specific | Custom `TestMethodAttribute` subclass |
| Skip in CI | `Assert.Inconclusive()` + `[TestCategory]` filter |
| Flaky API | `[Retry(n)]` (MSTest 3.8+) or custom attribute |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` (always runs) |
